<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOCKEYS SEEM TO GET BETTER WITH AGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The national top-10 jockey standings contain some interesting information. All 
of the top six riders -- except (Eddie) Delahoussaye, and he has a national 
riding title -- are past Eclipse Award winners. All of the top six -- except 
(Jose) Santos -- are over 30 years old, and two of them -- (Angel) Cordero and 
(Laffit) Pincay -- are over 40. This seems to be one sport where the cream 
comes to the top -- and stays there. 
</P>
<P>
DON LOVE, Palm Springs 
</P>
</TEXT>
