<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEPPERDINE ROLLS PAST AIR FORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior guard Shann Ferch scored 19 points and had eight assists to lead 
Pepperdine to an 82-75 win over the Air Force Academy in the first round of the 
Ameritas tournament in Lincoln, Neb. 
</P>
<P>
Ferch led four Waves players in double figures -- Tom Lewis added 17, Craig 
Davis 16 and sophomore Doug Christie had 15 points and seven rebounds. Geoff 
Lear added a game-high 14 rebounds for the Waves. 
</P>
<P>
The Waves (1-1) will play Nebraska (2-2), a 117-79 winner over Harvard, in the 
championship game tonight 6. 
</P>
<P>
Guard Raymond Dudley led the Air Force with a game-high 31 points. He scored 22 
in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Air Force (1-2) cut a 14-point Pepperdine lead to 62-59 with 7:42 left, but the 
Waves went on a 9-2 run in the next 2:03 to seal the win. 
</P>
