<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 'POLITE BANDIT' GETS 28-YEAR PRISON TERM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man prosecutors dubbed the "Polite Bandit" because of his courteous manners 
while robbing small businesses was sentenced Friday to 28 years and 8 months in 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys Superior Court Judge Alan B. Haber imposed the sentence on Gary Allen 
Smith, 45, of Long Beach in connection with a string of 30 robberies, 18 of 
which occurred in the San Fernando Valley last spring. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors had asked that Smith be sentenced to 30 years, nine years less than 
the maximum, because Smith pleaded guilty before the case went to trial. Smith 
was arrested in April at a drug treatment center in Tarzana when his mother 
turned him in after her car was linked to several of the robberies, authorities 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
