<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIOLENCE POLARIZES EL SALVADOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FMLN "terrorists" attack the U.S.-supported government of El Salvador, while 
Contra "freedom fighters" attack the U.S.-opposed government of Nicaragua. I 
imagine the appellations are reversed in the media of, say, Cuba and Russia. 
</P>
<P>
When these threadbare and profoundly flawed pejoratives come from the mouths of 
official spokesmen, is it any wonder that negotiations fail? 
</P>
<P>
Does President Bush really believe that these characterizations are valid? How 
can we play a positive role in the resolution of these blood-soaked guerrilla 
wars while broadcasting such divisive misrepresentations? 
</P>
<P>
E.C. BRESSLER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
