<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOLS DON'T EXIST JUST TO TRAIN ATHLETES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pity the poor Los Angeles City high school football teams that will lose 
players just before playoff time because of academic ineligibility. Pity the 
coaches who demand that the players spend so much of their non-school time 
practicing. 
</P>
<P>
Judging from Lonnie White's column on Nov. 21, you would think that the high 
schools existed for the purpose of training athletes and not minds. Let's get 
our prioities straight. Students attend school to get an education first. 
Extra-curricular activites should be considered only after students have proven 
themselves capable of meeting their academic responsibilites. 
</P>
<P>
JIM HAYES, Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
