<P>
UNBEATEN DAMEWORTH FEATURED IN REGIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Having won his third consecutive state Division I cross-country championship 
last week, Bryan Dameworth of Agoura High will return to Fresno's Woodward Park 
today for the Kinney West regional. 
</P>
<P>
Dameworth, undefeated this season, will be gunning for his first West regional 
title after finishing eighth as a freshman in 1986 and second last year. 
</P>
<P>
The top eight finishers in each of the boys' and girls' races will qualify for 
next Saturday's national championships in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Other top local entries include Abe Valdez of Camarillo and Canyon teammates 
Dan Berkeland and Dave Hartman. That trio finished fourth, fifth and sixth in 
the state Division I race. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura junior Deena Drossin will attempt to improve on her fifth-place 
performance of last year in the girls' race. 
</P>
