<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lockheed to Close Unit: Lockheed Corp. said it will close a money-losing New 
Jersey unit and lay off 950 workers after the unit failed to win new business 
from the government in heated competition. Lockheed said it will consolidate 
operations at Plainfield, N.J.-based Lockheed Electronics Co. with another 
affiliate, Sanders Associates of Nashua, N.H., by May 1. 
</P>
