<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNGARY PLANS TO SLASH ARMED FORCES 25% OVER 2 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUDAPEST, Hungary 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prime Minister Miklos Nemeth said Friday that Hungary will slash its armed 
forces by up to 25% in the next two years, scrapping many offensive weapons and 
regrouping them away from its western frontier. 
</P>
<P>
He also announced a shake-up in the defense command, replacing the army chief 
of staff and dismissing three deputy ministers. 
</P>
<P>
The cuts in hardware and personnel are on top of a 9% reduction announced last 
January. 
</P>
