<P>
.S. Army helicopter on night maneuvers crashed near this town, killing the 
pilot and injuring another crew member, the Army said Friday. Neither was 
identified. 
</P>
<P>
The Army said the accident occurred Thursday when the OH-58C helicopter hit a 
cable attached to a high-tension-wire pylon. 
</P>
<P>
In Washington, Rep. Frank McCloskey (D-Ind.) said the Army told him the crash 
took place during a night-vision goggles mission. He has urged an investigation 
into the safety of the goggles. 
