<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
NEW HOTELS ON WAY IN DISNEYLAND AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-story, 750-suite hotel is on its way to the Disneyland area after gaining 
Planning Commission approval. 
</P>
<P>
The 350,000-square-foot hotel will be built on the northwest corner of Harbor 
Boulevard and Orangewood Avenue and will be accompanied by a five-level parking 
garage. Two restaurants, meeting rooms and banquet rooms will be part of the 
hotel. 
</P>
<P>
The developer, Anaheim Hotel Complex of San Dimas, will build on a five-acre 
parcel that is vacant. 
</P>
<P>
The commission also approved plans for replacing the 100-room Space Age Lodge 
with a four-story, 169-room hotel. The old hotel at 1176 W. Katella Ave. will 
be demolished to make way for the new structure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
